It's so sleek. I love how you're just piloting a big tube of fairing in Stage 2... then you have all that stuff inside there...

That thing could be an awesome launcher, y'know? Does it just barely make orbit with the payload you used in the Imgur album, or did you already test the lifting capabilities? Or, you can do the math, I guess... but you're probably not Wernher von Braun, no offense...

Anytime. I never get feedback, so I give to others.
Oh and, it can carry practically anything, it has enough fuel to go kerbin escape, but not enough fuel to navigate to any other celestial bodies like Duna.

Very nice. I`m waiting for when fairings and bespoke tanks are stock then craft like this (and a lot of mine) can join the glorious stock master race.

Welcome to the forum.
Look good? Are you kidding? It's a thing of beauty! Well-designed, and very pleasing to the eye, not mention functional! Nicely done!
It looks nice and is apparently functional. That makes it a good rocket indeed. Well done!

Sadly this rocket has been discontinued, It's been officially deleted in a big mod migrate I've gone through.

The reason why it has been discontinued is because I don't plan on returning to the mun again, I've already mined all of the science I can out of it on career.

Planning on launching a final single man mun mission just to put a flag saying "Kerturn X memorial."

Now I'm focused on my space station project, which involves developing the vehicles that will be able to ferry up crew members.

I'll be sure to get some pics up of some of my latest spacecraft including my custom Orion orbiter/Ferry

Another reason I'm not using it any more, is because it's incapable of mining kethane, which I can easily set up a much heavier lander to do so, yea.

I'll also be building a minmus rocket called the Ogre, but that's for after I finish the space station project.

Edited March 23, 2014 by WindShieIds
